  "school": "ICT",
  "asset": "NQ1!",
  "timeframe": "1H / 15M / 1M (multi-timeframe)",
  "market_context": "NQ on 2/10/2023 around the New York open. On the hourly chart, equal highs sit above current price as buy-side liquidity, while ES had taken out a correlated low that NQ did not — creating an SMT divergence supporting a bullish bias.",
  "key_observation": "With hourly draw on liquidity sitting at equal highs and an SMT divergence at the lows, a 15-minute stop raid of an old low followed by a bullish closure provides a framework to drop to the 1-minute chart and enter at a discount targeting the equal highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the hourly chart, identify equal highs above price as the draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 2: Note the SMT divergence — ES swept a prior low while NQ did not — supporting bullish bias.",
    "Step 3: Drop to the 15-minute chart and wait for price to sweep an old 15M low (stop raid) opposite the draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 4: Confirm the sweep with a bullish candle closing back inside the range.",
    "Step 5: Drop to the 1-minute chart where price has displaced higher, leaving equal highs just before the New York open.",
    "Step 6: Mark the discount (lower half) of the 1-minute displacement range to enter long.",
    "Step 7: Reject the near 1:1 setup and require a minimum 1:2 risk-to-reward by adjusting entry/target.",
    "Step 8: Identify the 1-minute equal highs as the partial/take-profit objective at the New York open."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Anchor entries to a higher-timeframe draw on liquidity, use a 15-minute stop raid + bullish closure as confirmation, then enter at a 1-minute discount with a minimum 1:2 R, taking profits at structural liquidity like equal highs.",
